dmv.spring.demo.model.repository

Interface UserRepository

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    UserRepositoryJDBC

    public interface UserRepository
    CRUD operations for User entity. For all methods where receiving the User object as a parameter user id field is mandatory, otherwise that user can't be serviced.
    Author:
    dmv

      • create

        User create(User user)
        Store new user on persistence layer. Id will be generated and returned.

        User constraints: fields 'email', 'first name' and 'last name' must be provided; 'email' must be unique. If password was not given it will be generated and returned with the created object, otherwise password field will be null (for safety reasons).

        For user's roles the 'shortName' parameter is needed. If it is absent or the role with given name does not exist in database the IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.

        Parameters:
        user - A new user to persist
        Returns:
        persisted user on success
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if user or its id is null or user has incomplete or wrong information
        EntityAlreadyExistsException - if user with the same email already exists
        AccessDataBaseException - if operation was unsuccessful due to internal error

      • update

        User update(User user)
        Update existing user (found by id) with given user details (password and email fields are omitted, these are different operations).

        For user's roles the 'shortName' parameter is needed. If it is absent or the role with given name does not exist in database the IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.

        Parameters:
        user - An existing user with new details
        Returns:
        Update user (without a password)
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if user or its id is null or user has incomplete or wrong information
        EntityDoesNotExistException - if user can't be found
        AccessDataBaseException - if operation was unsuccessful due to internal error
